    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and shred the <strong>chicken</strong> apart with two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Once pulled, return the pan to a medium heat and add the<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml] </span><strong>water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the chicken is coated in a sticky sauce – this is your <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>hoisin free range chicken thigh</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1690285402079-x200.jpg",
